  RFC9843 [label="RFC9843
IGP Flexible Algorithms: Bandwidth,
Delay, Metrics, and Constraints
2025", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="Many networks configure the IGP link metric relative to the link capacity, and high bandwidth traffic gets routed per the link capacity. Flexible Algorithms provide mechanisms to create constraint-based paths in an IGP. This specification documents a generic metric-type and a set of bandwidth-related constraints to be used in Flexible Algorithms. This document updates RFC 9350."]; 

